    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "This length of silver chain has a tiger's fang on one end and the tip of a dire boar's tusk on the other. When you activate the chain, an ephemeral chain encircles the target creature's head and a cacophony of animal sounds clouds its mind. It must attempt a DC 35 Will save.",
        "level": 16,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Uncommon",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 159,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
                "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "uncommon"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Consumable",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 36,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 454",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 454",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 454,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "07336d377bbfcf8d760f34f32f513526",
                "text": "An item with this trait can be used only once. Unless stated otherwise, it\u2019s destroyed after activation. Consumable items include alchemical items and magical consumables such as scrolls and talismans. A character can Craft consumable items in batches of four.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Incapacitation",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 93,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 457",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 457",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 457,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "b26076555c07646f046dd58e7d5b3885",
                "text": "An ability with this trait can take a character completely out of the fight or even kill them, and it\u2019s harder to use on a more powerful character. If a spell has the incapacitation trait, any creature of more than twice the spell\u2019s rank treats the result of their check to prevent being incapacitated by the spell as one degree of success better, or the result of any check the spellcaster made to incapacitate them as one degree of success worse. If any other effect has the incapacitation trait, a creature of higher level than the item, creature, or hazard generating the effect gains the same benefits.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Magical",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 103,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 458,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
                "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Talisman",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 155,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "GM Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core pg. 263",
                            "alt": "GM Core pg. 263",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        },
                        "page": 263,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "ff9aabb4704b8d99cb4cd097aeab3b19",
                "text": "A talisman is a small object affixed to armor, a shield, or a weapon (called the affixed item). You must be wielding or wearing an item to activate a talisman attached to it. Once activated, a talisman burns out permanently.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            }
        ],
